claims:
5. A method for quantification of activated RelA in a cellular extract comprising the steps of:
providing the cellular extract comprising an unknown amount of the activated RelA;
contacting the cellular extract with one or more beads or a probe comprising one or more immobilized oligonucleotide sequences capable of binding the activated RelA, wherein the oligonucleotide sequence is selected from at least one of of SEQ ID NO: 9, SEQ ID NO: 10, SEQ ID NO: 11, SEQ ID NO: 12, SEQ ID NO: 13, SEQ ID NO: 14, SEQ ID NO: 15, SEQ ID NO: 16, SEQ ID NO: 17 or SEQ ID NO: 21;
binding the activated RelA with the one or more oligonucleotide sequences on the bead or the probe;
releasing the activated RelA bound to the oligonucleotide sequences from the one or more beads or the probe; and
assaying the released RelA by one or more analytical techniques.
